         <component>
            <section ID="L373d8ac3-f1e5-48a1-9a24-2ee47b1d66f4">
               <id root="e26ac509-cab5-4f56-9e0a-9010cb391dc1"/>
               <code code="34089-3" codeSystem="2.16.840.1.113883.6.1" displayName="DESCRIPTION SECTION"/>
               <title>DESCRIPTION:</title>
               <text>
                  <paragraph>Tobramycin ophthalmic solution is a sterile topical ophthalmic antibiotic formulation prepared specifically for topical therapy of external infections.</paragraph>
                  <paragraph>EACH mL CONTAINS:</paragraph>
                  <paragraph>ACTIVE: Tobramycin 3 mg (0.3%). INACTIVES: Boric Acid, Sodium Sulfate, Sodium Chloride, Tyloxapol and Purified Water. Sodium Hydroxide and/or Sulfuric Acid may be added to adjust pH (7.0 - 8.0).</paragraph>
                  <paragraph>PRESERVATIVE ADDED: Benzalkonium Chloride 0.1 mg (0.01%).</paragraph>
                  <paragraph>The structural formula of tobramycin is</paragraph>
                  <renderMultiMedia referencedObject="L27b1eed1-a1a1-4671-9d50-ce4d6d6364b3"/>
                  <paragraph>Molecular formula: C18H37N5O9 </paragraph>
                  <paragraph>Molecular weight: 467.52</paragraph>
                  <paragraph>Chemical name:</paragraph>
                  <paragraph>O-[3-amino-3-deoxy—α-D-gluco-pyranosyl-(1 → 4)]-O-[2,6-diamino-2,3,6-trideoxy-α-D-ribohexo-pyranosyl- (1 → 6)]-2-deoxystreptamine.</paragraph>
                  <paragraph>Tobramycin is a water-soluble aminoglycoside antibiotic active against a wide variety of gram-negative and gram-positive ophthalmic pathogens.</paragraph>
                  <paragraph>
                     <linkHtml href="http://dailymed.nlm.nih.gov/dailymed/drugInfo.cfm?setid=a5693ec9-d2f7-4d45-90b0-a113c54840d7">Close</linkHtml>
                  </paragraph>
               </text>
               <effectiveTime value="20141217"/>
               <component>
